---
// Code of Conduct Modal
---

<div
	id="coc-modal"
	class="hidden fixed inset-0 bg-black bg-opacity-50 flex items-center justify-center z-50 p-4"
>
	<div class="bg-white rounded-lg max-w-2xl w-full max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto shadow-xl">
		<!-- Header -->
		<div
			class="sticky top-0 bg-white border-b border-slate-200 px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between"
		>
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Code of Conduct</h2>
			<button
				onclick="toggleModal('coc-modal')"
				class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-700 text-2xl leading-none"
				aria-label="Close"
			>
				âœ•
			</button>
		</div>

		<!-- Content -->
		<div class="px-6 py-6 space-y-8">
			<p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: November 2025</p>

			<!-- Section 1 -->
			<section>
				<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span
						class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 text-sm font-bold"
						>1</span
					>
					Our Commitment
				</h3>
				<p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
					CodePals is committed to providing a welcoming and inspiring community for all. We pledge
					that everyone will be treated with respect and dignity.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- Section 2 -->
			<section>
				<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span
						class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 text-sm font-bold"
						>2</span
					>
					Our Standards
				</h3>
				<p class="text-slate-700 mb-3">
					Examples of behavior that contributes to creating a positive environment include:
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-2 ml-8 text-slate-700">
					<li>Being respectful and constructive in communications</li>
					<li>Being welcoming and supportive of newcomers</li>
					<li>Focusing on what is best for the community</li>
					<li>Showing empathy towards other community members</li>
					<li>Respecting differing opinions, viewpoints, and experiences</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<!-- Section 3 -->
			<section>
				<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span
						class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 text-sm font-bold"
						>3</span
					>
					Unacceptable Behavior
				</h3>
				<p class="text-slate-700 mb-3">Unacceptable behaviors include:</p>
				<ul class="space-y-2 ml-8 text-slate-700">
					<li>Harassment, intimidation, or discrimination</li>
					<li>
						Offensive comments related to gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability,
						mental illness, neuroatypicality, physical appearance, body size, race, age, regional
						discrimination, or religion
					</li>
					<li>Unwelcome comments regarding a person's lifestyle choices and practices</li>
					<li>Deliberate misgendering or use of "dead" or rejected names</li>
					<li>Gratuitous or off-topic sexual comments or imagery</li>
					<li>Physical contact and simulated physical contact without consent</li>
					<li>Threats of violence or violent language directed against another person</li>
					<li>Incitement of violence or harassment towards any individual</li>
					<li>Sustained disruption of community, meetings, or events</li>
					<li>Publishing of private information (doxxing)</li>
					<li>Unwelcome sexual attention</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<!-- Section 4 -->
			<section>
				<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span
						class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 text-sm font-bold"
						>4</span
					>
					Enforcement
				</h3>
				<p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
					Community managers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing our standards of
					acceptable behavior. When an individual engages in unacceptable behavior, community
					managers may take action they deem appropriate, up to and including temporary ban or
					permanent expulsion from the community.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- Section 5 -->
			<section>
				<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span
						class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 text-sm font-bold"
						>5</span
					>
					Scope
				</h3>
				<p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
					This Code of Conduct applies within all spaces managed by CodePals, including official
					channels, events, and any other spaces created by the community while conducting CodePals
					business.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- Section 6 -->
			<section>
				<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span
						class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 text-sm font-bold"
						>6</span
					>
					Reporting Violations
				</h3>
				<p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
					If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it to the community
					moderators. Reports can be made confidentially and will be handled with care and
					discretion.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- Section 7 -->
			<section class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-8">
				<h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
					<span
						class="w-6 h-6 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-primary-600 text-sm font-bold"
						>7</span
					>
					Contact & Support
				</h3>
				<p class="text-slate-700">
					To report violations or for questions about this Code of Conduct, please contact us on
					<a
						href="https://discord.gg/nhyzGV7u"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
						class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-semibold">Discord community</a
					>
					or create an issue on
					<a
						href="https://github.com/rmjoia/codepalsio"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
						class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-semibold">GitHub</a
					>.
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>

		<!-- Footer -->
		<div class="sticky bottom-0 bg-slate-50 border-t border-slate-200 px-6 py-4 flex justify-end">
			<button
				onclick="toggleModal('coc-modal')"
				class="px-4 py-2 bg-primary-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-600 font-medium transition-colors"
			>
				Close
			</button>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
